ABL.caption: rendered
ABL.doc: Fired when a viz first becomes interactive
ABL.name: rendered

ABM.caption: URL Set
ABM.doc: Raised when a URL action occurs.
ABM.name: urlset

AAG.caption: Device
AAG.doc: Specifies a device layout for a dashboard, if it exists. Values can be default, desktop, tablet, or phone. If not specified, defaults to loading a layout based on the smallest dimension of the hosting iframe element.
AAG.name: device

AAH.caption: Disable Popups
AAH.doc: Indicates whether to suppress the execution of URL actions.
AAH.name: disablepopups

AAI.caption: Hide Tabs
AAI.doc: Indicates whether tabs are hidden or shown.
AAI.name: hidetabs

AAK.caption: Toolbar
AAK.doc: Specifies the position of the toolbar, if it is shown. The values can be Toolbar.Top, Toolbar.Bottom or Toolbar.Hidden. If not specified, defaults to Toolbar.Bottom.
AAK.name: toolbar

AAL.caption: Touch Optimize
AAL.doc: Indicates whether to touch optimize viz controls.
AAL.name: touchoptimize

AAp.caption: Hide Web Edit
AAp.doc: Indicates whether the Edit button is hidden or visible. If not set, defaults to false, meaning that the Edit button is visible.
AAp.name: hideweb

AAq.caption: Hide Desktop Edit
AAq.doc: Indicates whether the Edit in Desktop button is hidden or visible. If not specified, defaults to false, meaning that the Edit in Desktop button is visible.
AAq.name: hidedesktop

AAr.caption: Suppress Default Edit
AAr.doc: Indicates whether the default edit behavior is suppressed. If not specified, defaults to false, meaning that the default edit behavior is not suppressed.
AAr.name: suppressdefault

ABN.caption: URL
ABN.doc: The URL associated with the event.
ABN.name: url
